thread.title: Ravens Kicker Justin Tucker Sinks Into Turf During Attempted Field Goal
thread.title_full: Ravens Kicker Justin Tucker Sinks Into Turf During Attempted Field Goal

author: Kelly Terez
title: Ravens Kicker Justin Tucker Sinks Into Turf During Attempted Field Goal
text:
Share Article 
Patrick Smith/Getty Images (SANTA CLARA, Calif.) -- The turf at Levi's Stadium practically swallowed Baltimore Ravens kicker Justin Tucker mid-kick. 
On Sunday in a game against the San Francisco 49ers, Tucker went in for the kick for a 45-yard field goal when his planted foot got stuck in the turf. 
According to ESPN, this marked the third miss of the second-most accurate kicker in the National Football League in his last 10 attempts. 
Many fans are blaming Levi's Stadium's turf, which isn't good for the NFL considering the year-old and $1.4 billion stadium is set to host the next Super Bowl.
